15 July 1694
London Wall & Will Kent
S my last to you was 12 curt to which referre you, & principally to
that of p ditto about the spas clothes of wich send patt as soon
as a pack bee made up, & I shall order you ut to ship them, for
I see no appearence yett of a convoy for ostend, whoever if anney
should present you shall doe well, to ship all what I ordered to buy
in london, now have before mee yours of 29 past, seeinge you can not
finde the fine chestant nor draptis browns, so lett them there
& buy ouly, what I further ordered, of which I desin the patt p
vere first, that I know what to order more for the winter the
convoy from london for Rott are malhenieuseley sunck, & if
the duitsh & English will not dake care for their coust
wee must trade no more, this a shame for the nation, that the french
play to the master, inclosed £200:, att 2 uso on S Joseph herne
& £ 200:- in an other bill of due ormons on my Richard lassels
of 3 cur att seight for which procure the needfuel & as soon
as in cas remitt ie valeu of that £200 for Amst, or in case
of non acceptance returne presentley with protest you give
